description:
Recently sold: $685,000. FEATURES
5 Bed  -  4 Bath  -  3 Stalls  -  4,760 Sq. Ft.  -  1.6 Acres

*Price includes a $50,000 base build out budget to bring LL to finished marketable status and to be completed by Seller prior to closing. Could be purchased for $699,500 with unfinished basement.*

HIGHLIGHTS
Big Open Gourmet Kitchen with Granite & SS Appliances - Custom Alder Built-ins & Millwork - Brazilian Cherry Floors - Living Room with Large Picture Windows & Gas Fireplace - Spacious Mudroom with Lockers & Laundry Access - Four Bedrooms Upstairs with En-suite Baths - Geothermal - In-Floor Heat in Master Bath - Sprinkler System -  Invisible Fencing - Large Deck with Rear Stair to Lawn - Private Backyard with Lush Landscaping & Firepit - Mature Trees 

IMPROVEMENTS
Exterior Paint - 842 Feet of Concrete Landscape Edging - Native Prairies with Wild Flowers - New Washer, Dryer, Fridge & Dishwasher

LOCATION
Quiet Cul-de-sac - Executive Neighborhood of 11 Homesites - 24 Acres of Association Owned Grounds with 4-Wheeling Trails / Walking Paths - Bridge Access to Neighborhood Pond for Skating / Hockey - Close Proximity to Crow-Hassan Park Reserve Hiking Trails, Dog Park, Horseback Riding Trails & Camping - Pheasant Acres Golf Club

Recently sold: $292,500. Pride in ownership! Immaculate 4BR, 2BA home on nearly one acre! Fantastic fenced yard includes gorgeous landscaping, mature trees, in ground pool & a 22x14 barn style shed for storage. This meticulously maintained home is priced to sell, so do not miss out!

Recently sold: $775,000. 10 Minutes from Medina! Executive style two story in private setting! Enjoy beautiful lake views and maple trees in the wooded back yard retreat. Open floor plan with custom design kitchen with 2 sub zero refrigerators and a wolf range with indoor grill. Home office on main level with fireplace. Room to expand in the lower level partially finished basement with 9ft ceilings "over 6,000 sq. ft with finished basement!" Convenient commute to Minneapolis as well as only 15 min to shopping in downtown Plymouth, Maple Grove and Ridgedale.  Acres of fun and a back yard built for entertaining.  Large flagstone fire-pit. 3 private schools close by. Horse boarding and miles of trails nearby! Public access to 2 lakes with great fishing within 1.5 miles. Heated 4+ car garage, to store all your toys. 3 zone heating. 400 amp service. Saltwater pool with auto cover equals low maintenance. Stamped concrete driveway, patio, and pool deck. Motivated Sellers! Bring Offers!

Recently sold: $500. Calling all small business owners and outdoor Enthusiasts! One of a kind Home/Shop/Acreage! Complete Remodel. Historic charm, with fantastic updates! In-Floor heat house & shop. Shop includes office,2 baths, and Huge Rec Room W/Kitchenette.

description:
Recently sold: $380,000. Main Level
* Welcoming open front foyer with closet.
* Gleaming hardwood floors flow from foyer to kitchen and dinette.
* Kitchen features generous cabinetry, stainless steel appliances, breakfast bar with seating, above the sink window, vaulted ceiling, workstation, pendant and under cabinet lighting.
* Sun splashed dinette offers tranquil views of backyard and easy access to deck making outdoor cooking and entertaining a joy.
* Formal living room with vaulted ceiling and front yard views.
* Family room features floor-to-ceiling brick gas fireplace and wall of windows offering serene year-round pond views.
* Conveniently located bedroom or office.
* Laundry room includes utility sink, cabinets, window, coat hooks, closet and garage entry. 
* 3/4 bath.
Upper Level
* Master suite offers ceiling fan, walk-in closet and peaceful views.  Master bath with tile floor, spacious vanity countertop, windows, tile surround soaking tub with stone backsplash and separate shower.
* 3 bedrooms on one level. All bedrooms have ceiling fans.
* Full bath with tiled floor.
Lower Level
* Spacious amusement room with recessed lighting and walk-out to patio.
* Recreation room offers recessed lighting and built-in shelving to keep you organized.
* Secondary bedroom with so many options.
* 1/2 bath with tile floor ~ plumber for future shower.
Additional Features
* Main level deck with gas line to grill and new steps to lower level deck with newer Hot Springs Vanguard Hot Tub.
* Paver patio with fire-pit and paver steps to backyard.
* Professional landscaping.
* 2018 Top of the Line Bryant Furnace/AC/Humidifier/Smart Thermostat
* New light switches and outlets, new light fixtures including 3 Hunter ceiling fans and lights kits in upstairs bedrooms.
* 2 car garage has extensive space for storage.
* Park just steps away.
All information deemed reliable but not guaranteed.

description:
Recently sold: $378,000. Long Beautiful Views of Jubert Lake and Countryside
MAIN LEVEL

Foyer
Welcoming you into the home is the large tiled foyer. It has plenty of space to move around, a door leading to the garage, and a large walk-in closet.

Living Room
Coming up the stairs is a welcoming living room with vaulted ceilings, massive picture windows, carpet, and open to the informal dining room.

Informal Dining Room
Open to the kitchen and living room, the informal dining room has the continuing vaulted ceiling and a large window allowing for natural light. 

Kitchen
The kitchen boasts spacious granite counters, a breakfast bar, a large pantry, a built-in desk, and plenty of cabinet space.

4-Season Porch 
The 4-season porch is gorgeous and a warming place to hang out and enjoy the views. It contains a gas fireplace, a vaulted knotty pine ceiling, carpet, windows surrounding the entire room (including trapezoid windows), a ceiling fan, recessed lighting, and a sliding glass door leading to the deck and backyard.
Master Bedroom 
The master has a large double closet, carpet, ceiling fan, and a walk-through full tiled bath.
Bedroom 2
The second bedroom is carpeted, has a large window, and is located adjacent to the full bathroom.
LOWER LEVEL
Family Room 
A perfect place for entertaining! This family room is carpeted, has wainscoting around the room, and large windows.


Bedroom 3 & 4
The lower level bedrooms are large, carpeted, windows allowing for plenty of light, closets, and located conveniently next to a large ¾ tiled bathroom with a large linen closet.
